reconsider familiar topics, including the Paris Peace Conference and Canada’s involvement with the United Nations, they enlarge the scope of Canada’s international history by subject, geography, and methodology. By demonstrating that race is a fundamental component of Canada and its international history, this important book calls for reengagement with the histories of those marginalized in, or excluded from, the historical record.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRacexPolitical aspectszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aRacexSocial aspectszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aGorman, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHastings, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLackenbauer, P. Whitney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadokoro, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadokoro, Laura, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcKenzie, Francine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcKenzie, Francine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMeren, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeren, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMills, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpooner, Kevin A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTouhey, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWebster, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYu, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://